        <p>April 17, 2020</p>

<p>Dear Thornton Fractional 215 Families:</p>

<p><br>
On Friday, April 17, 2020, Governor Pritzker announced that remote learning in Illinois would be extended through the end of the 2019-2020 school year to slow the spread of COVID-19. So you are aware, a remote learning day is defined by the Illinois State Board of Education (ISBE) as an educational program designed to provide continuation of learning for students under conditions that prohibit the learner and instructor from being in the same physical space. We are amending our existing eLearning plans to accommodate the guidelines established by ISBE.</p>

